What is Hybrid Bonding Technology?
Hybrid Bonding Technology is an advanced semiconductor packaging technique that combines multiple bonding methods—such as mechanical, chemical, and thermal processes—to create high-density, high-performance interconnects between wafers or dies. Unlike traditional methods, hybrid bonding enables direct copper-to-copper or oxide-to-oxide connections at a microscopic scale, resulting in superior electrical performance, enhanced thermal management, and significantly reduced interconnect pitch.
This technology is a cornerstone of modern 3D integration and advanced packaging solutions, critical for applications like CMOS Image Sensors (CIS), High Bandwidth Memory (HBM), and next-generation processors. It allows for the vertical stacking of chips, dramatically increasing processing power and efficiency while minimizing the device footprint.
